### Conceptual handoff checklist (NL)

- **Scope:** Read-only witness chain for **control selection** outcomes — `SelectionWitnessEnvelope_v0` → `SelectionGateAdvisory_v0` → `ControlSelectionDigest_v0` — extending [[phase-4-1-4-control-read-model-and-golden-row-selection-contract-roadmap-2026-03-27-0320]]; no sim-write or command-path commits (**D-060** presentation read-model / query-plane only).
- **Behavior:** Witness records `SelectedGoldenRows_v0` + `tick_key` (+ correlation id for trace join); advisory derives HOLD/OPEN/UNKNOWN from witness + `gate_policy`; digest surfaces labels with copy that **forbids** implying REGISTRY-CI PASS or HR thresholds.
- **Interfaces:** Inputs/outputs named in contract table; telemetry may use span-like structured events (**D-027** illustrative); policy enforcement stays outside the observability layer.
- **Edge cases:** Missing `gate_policy` version → UNKNOWN advisory; witness without selection → explicit empty witness (no silent PASS); D-032/D-043 replay literals and preimage work remain **OPEN_STUB** — not implemented in this slice.
- **Open questions:** Lane-C replay-and-verify wiring and replay literal freeze remain deferred per checklist item below; canonical registry binding follows vault decisions, not this observability slice.
- **Pseudo-code readiness:** Junior-facing Given/When/Then acceptance lines live under **Research integration** and synthesis [[Ingest/Agent-Research/phase-4-1-5-junior-handoff-2026-03-27-1200.md]]; execution repo layout **TBD** on execution track.

### Acceptance checklist (conceptual)

- [x] Witness envelope and advisory gate outputs are explicitly read-only.
- [x] HOLD/OPEN semantics are described without CI closure claims.
- [x] Execution-deferred boundaries are explicit (`D-032`, `D-043`, REGISTRY-CI hold).
- [x] Replay literal-field freeze and canonical hash registry — **waived on conceptual_v1** with explicit decision **[[decisions-log]] D-141**; execution remains **`@skipUntil(D-032)`** / D-043 preimage (lane-C harness **OPEN** on execution track; **no** REGISTRY-CI PASS / HR≥93 claim from this slice).

### Stale-output signal (conceptual, non-CI)

To support **D-060** / **stale_outputs** class without treating **`missing_roll_up_gates`** alone as a conceptual blocker:

- **`STALE_SURFACE_v0` (advisory):** operator-observable flag when **vault-represented** rollup/registry row metadata (wiki table + witness hooks) **diverges** from the last **D-060** / **`recal`** consistency stamp for the same phase slice — e.g. phase note amended after **`last_recal_consistency_utc`** without a matching audit row. Emitted only in **`ControlSelectionDigest_v0`** as **HOLD/OPEN** language; **never** a REGISTRY-CI PASS or HR≥93 claim.
- **Not** triggered by: validator **`needs_work`** on execution-deferred codes alone when **no** narrative/hash drift vs prior recal stamp exists (per conceptual_v1 advisory profile).

### Correlation join discipline

- **`selection_correlation_id`:** stable join key carried **verbatim** from `SelectionWitnessEnvelope_v0` → `SelectionGateAdvisory_v0` → `ControlSelectionDigest_v0` so audit replay can pair digest lines to witness rows without inferring order from timestamps alone.
- **Uniqueness:** one correlation id per **(tick_key, selection attempt)** tuple; retries mint a new id (prevents silent merge of partial retries in digest).

